value: Breeds in northeastern Asia and northwestern North America from eastern Siberia to Kamchatka and the Commander Islands; from Norton Sound, Alaska, to Washington; islands in Bering Sea and the Aleutian Islands. Winters southward to the coasts of China and Japan and from the Aleutian Islands to Lower California.
refer: Peter's Checklist of the Birds of the World

value: Vagrant: Morocco, 1 record El Hierro (Canary Is).

Rocky seacoasts and other coastal waters, nesting on flats and grassy slopes of islands, cliffs (breeding); beaches, rocky coasts, bays, estuaries, ocean over continental shelf, and garbage dumps in urban areas (nonbreeding).
